✨Myth vs fact✨ Read caption 

Myth: Physiotherapy is only for adults.
Fact: Physiotherapy is beneficial for individuals of all ages, from infants to older adults. Pediatric physiotherapy can address developmental delays, injuries, or congenital conditions in children, while geriatric physiotherapy focuses on maintaining mobility, independence, and quality of life in older adults.

Mind to Body, it affects you!!🙌🏻

Unlocking the intricate link between mental and physical health reveals a profound truth: our emotional well-being significantly influences our physical vitality. Stress, anxiety, and depression can manifest in physical symptoms, from headaches to digestive issues, highlighting the interconnectedness of mind and body. Nurturing our mental health through self-care, therapy, and mindfulness practices not only improves our psychological resilience but also fosters a healthier physical state. Recognizing and addressing the impact of mental health on our bodies empowers us to pursue holistic wellness, embracing the harmony between our mental and physical selves.

If I have to choose 3 foods to reduce JOINT PAIN
Why? Read the caption!

🥜 Nuts 

🫐 Berries: Berries such as strawberries, blueberries, and raspberries are packed with antioxidants and vitamins that can help reduce inflammation. They also contain compounds like anthocyanins, which have been shown to have anti-inflammatory effects, potentially providing relief from joint pain.

🥬 Leafy Greens: Leafy greens like spinach, kale, and Swiss chard are high in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants, including vitamin E, vitamin C, and beta-carotene. These nutrients have anti-inflammatory properties that can help reduce inflammation and alleviate joint pain.

Fact: Taping can provide support and stability, but it’s not a cure-all. Proper diagnosis and treatment by a healthcare professional are essential

‼️ The myths of Warm-ups‼️ Read caption 👇🏻

Warm-ups before high intensity exercise have been shown to INCREASE the risk of injury.

However, including static or dynamic stretching into warm-ups does NOT seem to either improve performance or reduce injury risk.

🌸 Spring! Hello Spring! 👋 Now that you're here, please send some blue skies and sunshine our way soon! 🙏🌿⠀
⠀
🌸 E's kindergarten celebrated 100 Days of School and she was the cutest little wanna-be 100-year-old grandma I ever did see 👵🏻💕⠀

⠀

 ⠀
🌸 The Mirror Mirror Experience by @momentfactory (in Calgary until Apr 14)⠀
⠀
🌸 #52hikechallenge Update: In March, we completed hikes 37-43 of the #52hikechallenge2023 . We've been hiking once in the first week of April, so we're now sitting at 44/52 hikes completed. ⠀
Wishing you the sweetest April!⠀

OUR SPRING BOOKSHELF 🌿⠀
⠀
1️⃣ The Spring Rabbit, by Angela McAllister⠀
⠀⠀
Spring wakes up after a long sleep and chases the cold weather away. She finds a frail little bird in the snow and saves him by turning him into a rabbit. This is a tale of how the Easter bunny came to be, with cute, quirky, and colourful illustrations.⠀
⠀⠀
2️⃣ Brambly Hedge: Spring Story, by Jill Barklem⠀
⠀⠀
The mice who live in Brambly Hedge plan a spring picnic as a birthday surprise for one of the Toadflax children.⠀
⠀⠀
3️⃣ The Country Bunny and the Little Gold Shoes, by Du Bose Heyward + Marjorie Hack⠀
⠀⠀
Originally written in 1939, this is a classic Easter tale of how a country bunny dreams of becoming an Easter bunny when she grows up, and how she is eventually selected to deliver eggs to children around the world.⠀
⠀⠀
4️⃣ The Dragon Easter Egg, by Didi Dragon + Maria Mau⠀
⠀⠀
Lucy finds a dragon's egg while on her family's annual Easter Egg hunt. It hatches a mischievous little dragon, making her Easter day the most magical and memorable one yet!⠀⠀
⠀⠀
5️⃣ Let's Make Rabbits, by Leo Lionni⠀
⠀⠀
A fun story of two rabbits, one drawn by a pencil, and the other made from brightly coloured paper. This is a creative and clever picture book that is sure to inspire some really cute bunny art.⠀
⠀
6️⃣ Happy Easter, by Kurt Wiese⠀
⠀
Another classic, this one from 1952, that tells the story of a mother rabbit and her children who collect eggs from hen, with the intention of painting them and hiding them in peoples gardens for Easter. However, they are in for a very cute..and colourful surprise!⠀
⠀
7️⃣ Goodbye Winter, Hello Spring, by Kenard Pak⠀
⠀
A short and sweet seasonal story of spring's arrival.⠀
⠀
8️⃣ The Little Rabbit, by Nicola Killen⠀
⠀
Ollie and her toy bunny set out on an adventure, when a spring breeze wooshes past them, magically transforming bunny into a real live rabbit!⠀
⠀⠀

4 BOARDWALK TRAILS NEAR BANFF + CALGARY⠀⠀
⠀⠀
💾 Don't forget to save for your next mountain adventure!⠀
⠀⠀
A few of our favourite 𝗸𝗶𝗱-𝗳𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗱𝗹𝘆 boardwalk trails. 𝗔𝗹𝗹 𝟮 𝗸𝗺 𝗼𝗿 𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿!⠀
⠀⠀
1️⃣ MANY SPRINGS TRAIL, KANANASKIS⠀
⠀⠀
Located in Bow Valley Provincial Park,⠀
Many Springs Trail is a 1.6km interpretive wetland trail⠀
⠀
2️⃣ SULPHUR MOUNTAIN SUMMIT, BANFF⠀
⠀
Located in Banff, at the top of Sulphur Mountain, this 1 km (one way) boardwalk offers spectacular mountaintop views of Banff town and the surrounding mountains. You can either take the gondola up to the boardwalk, or hike up from the parking lot, which is an additional 5.5km (one way)⠀
⠀⠀
3️⃣ CAVE + BASIN BOARDWALK TRAILS, BANFF⠀
⠀
Located in Banff, the thermal waters around these boardwalks are home to a variety of exotic plant life, as well as fish, snakes, and snails, found nowhere else in Banff⠀
Upper Boardwalk (0.4km)⠀
Lower Boardwalk (0.5km)⠀
⠀
4️⃣ POLICEMAN'S CREEK, CANMORE⠀
⠀⠀
Located in the heart of Canmore, this easy 1.3km loop trail takes you on a wetland walk alongside Policeman's Creek. There are lots of options to extend this walk by staying on the connected pathways.⠀
⠀⠀

⠀
Monday greeted me with an inbox full of unread messages, a laundry basket, overflowing, and a to-do list that seems only ever to be growing, never shrinking. Eight-and-a-half years into my motherhood journey, mornings like these can be overwhelming. But my heart knows it was all worth it.⠀
⠀
Motherhood is a juggling act, and if I have to choose between spending my weekend doing chores, or being present and making memories, and I'll go with the later every single time (well, at least until we're out of clean clothes 😂). I can't do it all, and neither can you. And that's okay. ❤️⠀
⠀

5 MUST-SEE FROZEN WATERFALLS NEAR BANFF + CALGARY⠀
⠀
💾 Don't forget to save + add to your winter bucket list!⠀
⠀
A few of our favourite 𝗸𝗶𝗱-𝗳𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗱𝗹𝘆 frozen waterfalls and icefalls. All hikes are under 5km. ⠀
⠀
⚠️ In winter, footwear with traction (ice cleats/crampons/microspikes) is highly recommended on all hikes for both kids and adults.⠀
⠀
1️⃣ JOHNSTON CANYON⠀
⠀
Located about 30 minutes from Banff Town, along the Bow Valley Parkway. 1.2 km (one way) to Lower Falls (pictured), 2.5km (one way) from trailhead to Upper Falls.⠀
⠀
2️⃣ BOW FALLS⠀
⠀
Located in Banff town. You can park in the lot, located on River Ave, right next to the falls, or walk from downtown Banff (1.6 km one way). Please note that the stairs can be extremely icy in winter.⠀
⠀
3️⃣ GROTTO CANYON⠀
⠀
Located about 13 km east of Canmore, off of Highway 1, near the hamlet of Exshaw. It's a 4 km round-trip to the falls. The creek bed is iced over in winter, making this an ice walk. It's super slick in places! Try to spot the Hopi Pictographs on the canyon wall, dated to be 500-1000 years old.⠀
⠀
4️⃣ TROLL FALLS⠀
⠀
Located in Kananaskis, just off of Highway 40, not far from Nakiska and Kananaskis Village. The hike to Troll Falls is 1.7 km (one way). Try to spot the "troll face" in the rocks (on your LH side when facing the falls)⠀
⠀
5️⃣ MARMOT FALLS⠀
⠀
Located further up the trail from Troll Falls (same hike). Continue on from Troll Falls on the marked pathway. This section of the hike is steep and slippery! Our favourite part: You can walk behind the falls!⠀
⠀
𝟮 𝗕𝗢𝗡𝗨𝗦 𝗪𝗔𝗧𝗘𝗥𝗙𝗔𝗟𝗟𝗦 + 𝗜𝗖𝗘𝗙𝗔𝗟𝗟𝗦⠀
⠀
*️⃣ UPPER FALLS⠀
⠀
If you're already at Troll Falls, follow the marked trail, for just under 1 km more, up the hill. Trail is steep in places and slippery! Might be tricky for young kids.⠀
⠀
*️⃣ FISH CREEK ICE FALLS⠀
⠀
Not a waterfall, but these icefalls are located in Calgary. Park near Bow Valley Ranch. Head south on pathway that leads to the "Stream Changes Trail". Just before the bridge, turn right (west) off the main pathway onto a small trail that runs parallel to the creek. Follow trail along the creek until you get there!⠀
⠀

✨3 Ways…

As an introvert, I have found that I need to be a little more strategic when networking to get the most out of it and stay out of my head.

Here are 3 strategies that worked for me:

1️⃣ Gamify the experience for yourself: Create a challenge that you can keep track of internally. My go-to was setting a goal number of people I would talk to before I left. It pushed me to talk to people instead of standing in the corner.

2️⃣ Pick one thought-provoking question to ask everyone you talk to: Finding an interesting question to ask about a current event, industry hot topic, or trend can help you stand out when meeting others and be a great fallback when you run out of the typical small talk.

3️⃣ Focus on others and what value you can bring to them: I found that when I focus on the other person, looking for ways that I can bring value to them as we talk, it takes me out of my head and into the present moment. It’s also a great way to build deeper connections because people resonate with others who show they care.

What are some ways that you get the most out of networking?

How often do you intentionally meet your feelings?
How often do you intentionally check in with yourself and make sure that there is no unprocessed grief, pain, or anger left?

We avoid feeling because life is too busy, because we have to be productive, because we must do the right things, no space for feeling just yet.

And yet, the presence or absence of our emotional hygiene is the only thing that defines how in touch we are with ourselves. 

When you don’t know how you feel, or you haven’t felt anything for a while, when you don’t understand why your body is weaker than usual, why you don’t sleep well, when you are unsure why you can’t focus, or why do you have anxiety- 

I encourage you to meet your feelings first. 

In my FREE webinar “Shameless Self-Love,” I’m introducing you to the language that will set you on a path of creating beautiful relationships with yourself.

If you are ready- send me the word SHAMELESS to get instant access. 

Love always,
Dr. Amanda.

It’s a common thing because, for ages, women have been conditioned to believe that asking for more, desiring more, and aspiring to be/do/have is bad. 

Fearing rejection, some women chose to settle down for something that is not entirely aligned with their sincere needs and desires. 

And while you exist in that reality, you begin believing that it’s all there is.

Pay attention to when you feel that women around you unconsciously convince you to lower your standards, even if they have good intentions and deeply care about you.

Love and friendship are precious, but it’s imperative that you don’t lose the course of the life you are crafting, and are also surrounding yourself with women who desire more for you. 

In my FREE webinar about shameless self-love I will teach you how to stay on the right course. Watch it now: send me the word SHAMELESS and I’ll send you the direct access.
Love always,
Dr. Amanda

#midlifemuse #dramandahanson #amandahanson #quotes #quoteoftheday #selflove #therapist #psychologist #midlifeinfluencer #midlifeawakening #midlifeopportunity #womensupportingwomen #selfworth #greyhairinfluencer

Since I was a girl who didn’t have anyone to listen to her at the harshest time of her life, I decided to be that person for others. 

So, I dedicated my life to psychology. 

I love making people feel better. 
I love it when people feel relieved. 

But what I know for the fact after seeing things I’ve seen behind the doors of my office, is that it is absolutely necessary for us, women, to know, when to hide that smile and to demand being taken seriously. 

After ages of programming that a “good” woman is a pleasing woman, it can be very uncomfortable to be the first one who stops smiling. 

A lot of people are intimidated by women who don’t smile. 
We are shamed for being “angry,” “too much,” or “too serious.”

But what if we are not?

What if we are not smiling simply because we are sick and tired of people walking all over us, not taking our needs seriously, and not paying attention to our cries for help? 

Being respected, heard, and seen is a skill. 

Of course, I want to offer a solution to everyone.
You know that I have a FREE class about shameless self-love that allows you to remove conditioning, and I hope you will watch it. 

If you have, DM me, and let’s chat about what you saw, felt, and thought about. 

If you have not- send me the word SHAMELESS and I will send it to you.

Love always,

Dr. Amanda.

 And I don’t want you to ever think it’s too late for you to have it.

If you can get past the shame of not having a loving mother-daughter relationship you have the potential to completely change your whole fucking life!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So much of your identity is tied to this relationship that often times you feel powerless to see how anything could be any different.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So you live in the shame and humiliation of it. Healing allows you to create a new identity one that says you are lovable and worthy. It allows you to trust yourself and trust others.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💝But first you have to be honest and except the reality of what it is.

💝Then you allow the sadness and the grief of what will never be.

💝Then from there you’re able to re-create the life that you choose, one rooted in the peace of loving your self deeply.

Here are just a few benefits of healing from the painful relationship with your mother. 
👉🏾Asking for what you want without feeling guilty?
👉🏾Learning to be vulnerable and let people in.
👉🏾Finding supportive people who are waiting to be there for you?
👉🏾Being more patient and compassionate with yourself?
👉🏾Setting healthy boundaries without guilt & shame.

There are about 25k new people here 🤯…

So I thought this would be a great time for us to get to know each other better. 

Let’s start with the basics shall we…
My name is Jennifer Arnise
😍 I’m 49 yrs old
👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 My parents divorced when I was five.
♏️ Im a Scorpio (even though I don’t follow astrology much)
💙 In a solo parent have a 16 yo son
🤠 I’m from NC…a real country girl
🍾 I’ve lived in the Atl for almost 20 years
💔 My mama stopped speaking to me nine years ago when I confronted her about her behavior.

I always thought I was crazy, or making it all up. That was until I started telling my story on here and realized I wasn’t alone.

I was full of so much shame, anger and frustration. It wasn’t until I started doing my own healing work that I realize how deeply I had been affected by that relationship with mother.

I was bad with men, money and everything in between.🤦🏾‍♀️

This IG community is here to let any Black woman who had a painful relationship with her mother know that she is not crazy and she’s not alone.

I center the stories and experiences of Black women here. I center the healing and transformation of Black woman here. This is the work.

❤️‍🩹Your turn! Let me know in the comments what do you need help with on your healing journey?

Healing your mother wound is all about learning to build a healthy and loving relationship with your self. 

There’s a good chance you treat you how she treated you.

You think if you treat yourself like shit someone will come rescue you and tell you that you’re worth it. When in fact, you’ll only believe you’re worth it, when you start to treat yourself like you’re worth. 💞

Public Service Announcement 🗣️

Tread lightly in these comments if you come up in here with some bible thumpin, trauma centered, co-dependent, respect your parents, she did the best she could ass bs. 

I will never stop talking about this.

Lately believing in everything happens for a reason! And OH BOY, for much better!🤍

Childcare support for the self employed ✨

Get 20% of your childcare paid for as a self employed person as well as up to 30 free hours of childcare per week 🚨 

While the self-employed have drawn the short straw over the years when it comes to childcare and government support, the Tax-Free Childcare scheme could be just what you’re looking for. 

Tax free childcare ✨

Tax-free childcare is a scheme operated by the government to provide financial support for new parents with children in childcare up to the age of 11.

Parents can receive up to £2,000 per year for each child to help with the costs of childcare. 

If you qualify the government will contribute £2 for every £8 that you pay to your childcare provider. That’s 20% of your childcare covered up to £2,000 per year per child. 

30 hours free per week ✨

On top of this you might also qualify for up to 30 hours of free childcare if your child is between 2 and 4 years old. 

If your child is:

• 2 years old, you can get 15 hours free childcare
• 3 to 4 years old, you can get 30 hours free childcare

For both schemes ✨

If you’re self-employed and started your business less than 12 months ago
You can earn less and still be eligible for free childcare for working parents.

You need to be earning a minimum of £183 per week and a maximum of £1,923 per week. 

To apply ✨

Setup a childcare account with HMRC online today to apply.

The encrypted conversations 🔒 that happen behind the scenes of running a 7 figure business. Like a weekly photo dump but instead, come inside my incredibly humbling, hilarious & nerdy WhatsApp chats this week.

1. Weekly therapy is a core part of the routine that helps me to sustain myself & the businesses but I’d be lying if I said it didn’t feel like breaking myself to but myself back together again
2. As we approach the end of the personal tax year, here are some super simple quick tick tasks, which can help you extract up to £61,300 from your limited company, completely tax free which could save you up to £16,075 in corporation tax this year. 🚀
 
These are my top tax tips to action by 31st March 2024 💐:
 
	1.	Max out your pension contributions: Paying into a private pension is tax-efficient because you’ll reduce your company’s taxable profits and therefore your Corporation Tax liability. For the 2023-24 tax year, the pension allowance is £60,000, meaning you can add £60,000 into your private pension without paying any income tax, and you’ll save up to £15,000 in corporation tax by reducing your taxable profits

	2.	Claim your £300 trivial benefit allowance: As a director of a small business (with less than 5 shareholders) you can extract £300 from your business completely tax free, per director

	3.	Salary structure: if you’re setup for a directors only payroll, don’t forget to review your directors salary for the upcoming tax year

	4.	Claim your £1,000 dividend allowance: don’t forget that included in your dividends for the year, you have a tax free dividend allowance which for the 2023-24 tax year is £1,000

	5.	Review upcoming expenditure for capital allowances: in the UK we have lots of tax incentives to invest in assets this year, so if you’re planning on purchasing assets within your business, you might like to consider purchasing them before 31st March 2024 to get up to 100% tax relief in this financial year.

	6.	Book a financial MOT: pop time in your accountants diary to take a deep dive into these before the end of the tax year.

The Spring Budget explained! 🌼 

I’m bringing you TODAY’s budget bombshells and their impact on business owners. From tax updates to payroll shifts and more, I’ve got the lowdown on your evolving business landscape. 💼

Here’s what we’ve seen announced:

✨ VAT threshold increase to £90,000 from £85,000.
✨ Tax relief on leased assets
✨ National insurance cuts for employees and the self-employed
✨ Child benefit changes
 
Here’s the full debrief:
 
Tax updates specifically for business owners:
 
VAT threshold increase to £90,000 from £85,000.
 
The VAT threshold used to rise each year until 2017, if we take £85,000 when it was set in 2017 and apply inflation between now and then, a real world uplift would have seen the VAT threshold rise to £108,000 so whilst a £5,000 uplift will impact lots of business owners actually not a true uplift.
 
Payroll tax updates:
 
National insurance cuts - employees
Following a 2 percentage point cut in the Autumn Statement, the main rate of Employee National Insurance will be cut again by a further 2 percentage points from 10% to 8% in April – a one third reduction in the main rate of National Insurance which means the average worker on £35,400 will receive a tax cut of over £900 compared to last year.
 
National insurance cuts – self-employed
Following a 1 percentage point cut in the Autumn Statement, the main rate of Class 4 NICs for the self-employed will be cut by a further 2 percentage points from 8% to 6% from April - saving the average self-employed person on £28,000 over £650 compared to last year when combined with scrapping the requirement to pay Class 2 NICs announced at Autumn Statement.
 
Useful changes which aren’t tax, but wider business:
 
Child benefit changes
High Income Child Benefit Charge to be assessed on a household-basis by April 2026, and immediate support for working families by increasing the threshold to £60,000 and halving the rate at which Child Benefit is repaid – representing a £1,260 boost on average for around half a million working families.

HMRC have the right to check your personal and business records at any time, to make sure you’re paying the right amount of taxes across different areas of your business and personal affairs.
 
There are lots of different triggers for HMRC investigations. HMRC state that investigations are usually triggered when figures are filed that appear to be incorrect or suspicious in some way. However, there are some extra reasons that can mean that your business might be the target of an investigation:
 
💸 HMRC receives a tip-off
💸 You work in a high-risk industry, for example one that routinely takes cash payments
💸 You have a large fall in income, increase in costs or there are inconsistencies between different returns
💸 You file your returns consistently late
💸 Your costs are above the industry norm
💸 Your tax returns are inconsistent with your standard of living
💸 You are in a sector that HMRC has decided to target
 
HMRC can enquire to look at one or more elements of your business, the 6 most common things they’ll be looking at are:
 
💀 your corporation tax records, filings & tax paid if you’re a limited company
💀 your self-assessment accounts and tax calculations if you’re a sole trader
💀 your self-assessment tax return for one specific year
💀 your PAYE records, filings & tax paid if you’re an employer
💀 your VAT records, filings & tax paid if you’re VAT registered
💀 your CIS records, filings & tax paid if you’re part of the construction industry
 
If you do get notified that you’re being investigated by HMRC, the three things you should do straight away are:

1. check that the correspondence, is from HMRC and isn’t part of a scam
2. make a claim against your HMRC investigation insurance, if you have it
3. call your accountant

Food eliminations are not a root cause approach😐. I said it.

If you've been told by an "acne expert" you need to eliminate dairy, gluten, soy, peanuts, chocolate, sugar, etc. to heal your skin... That's a big ole 🚩🚩

Here me out. While food removals *might* be necessitated (short term OR if it's a true allergy), that must be a case by case basis and for most of our clients, we don’t implement food eliminations❌

But thanks to Google and the "experts" (🙄) , food eliminations are the most common thing women with acne try first. Sometimes, it does the trick and there’s a reason for that.

Skin flares [acne, psoriasis, eczema] are the symptom and it's frustrating as hell bc it's one that's visible for the world to see. i've been there. it sucks.

But you're smart enough to know there's a solution and you're body is presenting the symptoms for a reason. 

If you feel like certain foods trigger your acne, it's because there's something internally that's leading to it. Here's a few mechanisms that make food an acne trigger:
➡️ gut- immune system-skin mechanism
➡️ halogen mechanism
➡️ cellular metabolism mechanism

In order to heal your skin, rather than removing the trigger that's making the 🔥 worse how about you actually heal the internal environment? That's what will support clear skin LONG TERM. 

Because it's addressing the root cause💥

A root cause approach doesn't: 
❌ Blame the food without looking at the gut first
❌ Skips minerals
❌ Dismiss the essential step of calming inflammation
❌ Blindly supplementing without certainty on your nutrient needs

Instead, we make changes based on your exact physiological needs🎯

DM me CLEAR SKIN if you want to learn more about a personalized approach.
The steps that finally helped her clear her inflamed acne after trying everything...

POV: You tried THIS and started seeing improvements in your skin.

Minerals are electrolytes. Electrolytes are minerals. 

They are found everywhere in our body: inside our blood, in our cells, part of enzymes, part of our skin, hair, nails, bones, muscles.

Minerals run the body. 

Minerals make energy for our cells. 

They are the ‘spark plugs of our cells’. 

Every cell requires minerals to make & signal hormones, make enzymes and produce ENERGY⚡️

And when you start repleting such an important component to health, your body is like “THANK YOU. ILYSM. HERE’S SOME ENERGY”💥

Unpopular opinion: your acne isn't from imbalanced hormones. 

➡️ DM me CLEAR SKIN if you want to understand the deepest root causes of your hormonal acne. 

Hormones get a bad rap. 

But what we know about hormones is they are messengers. They are signaling molecules and while hormonal imbalances DO play a role in triggering acne in the skin, we have to understand what’s the trigger BEHIND the imbalance. 

If you have the hormonal acne checklist, 
✔️Jawline acne
✔️Cystic
✔️Shows up around your cycle
✔️maybe you have a PCOS diagnosis

Let me ask you, 
do you know what TYPE of hormonal imbalance is underneath your acne? & do you know what's CAUSING the hormones act whack?

bc THOSE are the questions needing answers.

Androgens? Progesterone? estrogen? Insulin? IGF-1? Thyroid? Cortisol? or a combination of a few of these?

Most of our clients think their acne is hormonal but when we do labs, it's ALWAYS more than that.

Client B asked those questions when she had cystic & cyclical jawline acne every month and sure, when we tested, her hormones were a mess.

but we looked deeper we found 3 big systems that were creating the hormonal mess.
✅ Metabolism
✅ Minerals
✅ Gut Health

Once she made the specific adjustments to correct the deeper issues. her hormones responded and then her skin cleared😎

THAT'S BIOLOGY, BB

Ready to stop blaming hormones & start getting results? DM me CLEAR SKIN & I’ll show ya how💋
Stubborn acne got ya feeling STUCK & you're trying EvErYtHiNg?👀 watch out for these common mistakes.

1- Add minerals in daily
Are you meeting your sodium, magnesium, and potassium needs or not so much? These minerals are involved in digestion, thyroid & insulin signaling (& sooo much more) - if deficient, this alone can be a big culprit to constant skin probs. (we run HTMA mineral testing at our practice and it's one of my fav ways to see what these minerals levels are inside the cells 📊)

2- Prioritize key skin nutrients
Vitamin A and E have roles as a major antioxidants + protecting against iron overload (which I see as a root cause of acne a LOT). They also boost progesterone, have anti-estrogen effects and help the skin heal. We don't blindly supp around here bc what your body needs is soooo individualized but these are 2 major key players in the skin conversation

3- Eat enough
Under eating over time slows down your metabolism > which slows down metabolic health > impacts gut health + skin health + hormone health. All of which contribute to chronic ongoing acne. Are you eating enough protein, fats, fiber and starches daily to meet your needs? Might be time to reassess.

4- Support your skin barrier topically
The surface of your skin has a microbiome too!! 🤯 There are bacteria that live on the surface that have a preference for a specfic pH so the products you use DO in fact impact your skin 

These are basic, non negotiable foundations. BUT if you've been around here for a while and you feel like you've already done these things and you're still not seeing the results you want, you have a 1 of 2 options:

-Option 1: Keep doing what you're doing. Maybe that's another supplement, another detox, another cleanse... (sounds like more guessing & checking IMO aka more 💰 you probably don't want to keep spending) Was that a bit harsh? Perhaps. But that's because Option 2 can actually get you somewhere.
- Option 2: Get a strategy to target the root cause of your acne. Get a team of practitioners who are trained to know what to look for to find the root cause and put a personalized plan together to help you clear your skin.

DM me CLEAR SKIN  if you’re ready for a PERSONALIZED strategy💃

Dismissed by your doctor again?😢
Defeated & frustrated bc you just want answers?😡
Overwhelmed by what the internet says?🤨

We hear these comments often.

Example: Our client had an inflammation lab 14 TIMES higher than normal. It was even flagged high on her conventional lab printout. Her doctors response: “I’ve seen levels in the 100’s so this isn’t that bad”

That’s bullshit. That’s not health care.

Because there was no easy answer to explain the cause or to “treat” it, she was told it was nothing to worry about.

Does chronic skin issues, constant fatigue, ongoing bloat feel like "nothing to worry about" to you?!

Our client deserved better and so do you.

You and I are not the types to accept that excuse though.

You advocate for yourself. You empower yourself with knowledge and a team that cares to dig deeper with you.

Many conventional lab ranges are based on “non-disease” states but we’re into OPTIMAL around here and I’m guessing you are too.

If you find yourself frustrated and stuck despite trying EVERYTHING for your skin, it's time to take a new approach. 

A root cause approach is it. How can I be so confident?

Well, it works because it's diving deep to look at the mechanisms BEHIND the symptoms you're experiencing. 

It's getting to the underlying issue not just throwing a bandaid over whatever's going on in the body. We're dialing in specifically what your body needs, but it’s from an inside out perspective.

And when you know EXACTLY what your body needs to resolve chronic skin symptoms, you:
🌟Feel empowered to take action
🌟Have confidence & clarity on what you’re doing
🌟START SEEING RESULTS

Want to address the ROOT CAUSE of your gut, skin, hormone symptoms and feel confidence in the action you’re taking towards optimal health. DM me CLEAR SKIN.

Fed up with hormonal acne? 

Here’s what you NEED to know to start healing your hormones. 

When I ask you what you think is causing your acne, most of the time I get 1 of 3 answers.
1. “My hormones”
2. “My gut”
3. “I have no idea”

And when you say hormones, I suspect you are referring mostly to sex hormones [estrogen, progesterone, testosterone] and you’re right. Imbalances in those can worsen acne.

But so can other hormonal issues. Like chronically high insulin or poor thyroid health.

But here’s the missing piece to heal hormones that you haveeeee to remember. 

📣 Hormones are NOT the root of the problem

Hormones are responding to cellular signals.

This means if we want to heal hormones we need to support the mechanisms behind them 

A PRIMARY component that is involved in cellular signaling is MINERALS. 

Minerals are like the spark plugs that our cells need to work properly

If the individual cell doesn’t have what it needs to ‘do the things’ (make energy, make enzymes, send messages, etc.) you’re DEF not going to see changes with your skin. 

Want to support your skin? Support your hormones✨

Want to support your hormones? Start with minerals✨

DM me MINGUIDE and I’ll show you how to get started👀

Why you removed a bunch of foods but saw NO skin changes 👀

➡️ DM me CLEARSKIN if you want to know more about what you can do to clear your skin. 

Of course overall nutrition impacts your skin but the internet will toss up a big list of foods to eliminate.

Our clients have come to us having tried dairy free, sugar free, low carb, keto, vegan, whole 30 and the list goes on....with zero results to show for it.

Food eliminations are not a root cause approach😐. I said it.

Here me out: While food eliminations *might* be necessitated (short term), it’s a case by case basis and for most of our clients, we don’t implement food eliminations❌

There are a few mechanisms that make food an acne trigger:
➡️ gut- immune system-skin mechanism
➡️ halogen mechanism
➡️ cellular metabolism mechanism

but here’s the thing- when you optimize gut, metabolism & minerals. You outsmart those triggers.

There are dozens of acne mechanisms.

➡️ If iron overload is your cause, removing foods won’t work.
➡️ If low progesterone is your cause, removing foods won’t work.
➡️ If gut infection is your cause, removing foods won’t work.
➡️ If high androgens is your cause, removing foods won’t work.
➡️ If sluggish biliary system is your cause, removing foods won’t work.

you get the point.

There’s no shame in this - 50% of adults have acne. You’re not doing anything wrong but trying things.

but if you want long term results, you need to address YOUR root causes💥

To do this, you need to:
✅ properly test

I’m not just talking test basic blood labs or hormones. Think deeper.

things like full iron recycling system labs, nutrient labs, gut bacteria, gut infections, biliary system labs, halogen labs, minerals⭐

Acne is not an antibiotic or accutane deficiency. It’s not your genetics or your cotton pillow case that’s keeping you from clear skin. It’s the fact that you’re not addressing your root cause(s)🚨

Ready to enjoy foods and NOT have to worry about a breakout? A personalized approach is it. DM me CLEAR SKIN

WHAT YOUR SKIN IS TELLING YOU

➡️ DM me CLEAR SKIN if you want help figuring out 🔍

Chronic acne is a symptom. 

Acne is your body’s getting your attention. It’s annoying. it’s frustrating.

Yes, a pimple here and there is normal - pores are pores.

but if you feel stuck with chronic acne, inflamed skin, painful pimples and you’ve been told:
❌ it’s just genetics
❌ you’ll have it your entire life
❌ there’s nothing you can do

that’s bullshit.

Targeting your root cause is the key to calming your acne from the inside out, without a gazillion pills or a crazy restrictive diet 🤩

Trust me, it’s not as daunting as it seems. If you’re tired of not seeing the results you crave, do you know how to:

✔️Pinpoint the root cause(s) of YOUR acne?
✔️Tailor a clearing plan to YOUR unique needs based on those root causes?

After years of working with hundreds of women (& my own skin journey), what I’ve learned is this:

Skin is communication. 

To finally clear your skin you need to figure out what your body is telling you & ID what’s going on🔎🔎

❓Is gut barrier intact and supported?
❓Is mineral status and resiliency compromised? 
❓Are nutrients + minerals being digested + absorbed to adequately support cellular health and signaling?

❓Do you have a proper topical routine to support a strong skin barrier?

caption: Who needs a Valentine when u have a Galentine 👯‍♀️🩷

My best things in 2023 >> 

* Getting the opportunity’s to do what I love all the time!! 🎬 Acting is my passion and what makes me truly happy and in 2023 I worked on more projects than ever before. ⭐️ I also want to thank @dharmannstudios for all the videos and my new series that will be continuing into 2024!! 🎥

*  I starred in my first movie releasing in mid 2024 😆 (you guys will hear all about it soon) and spent three weeks in Rhode Island with an incredible crew and cast filming. My heart was so happy doing what I love ❤️ 

* YOU GUYS!!! 📈📈 I cannot thank you all enough for the insane growth and support on my platforms this year! I can’t wait to continue growing in 2024 💗

* Getting to create, edit, and post content for you guys kept me busy in the best way this year, let me know what kind of videos you wanna see in 2024!! 📲

* Spending time with my family <3 I love u all so much 🫶

* Traveling the world 🌎 I feel so blessed to be able to travel to many different places every year 🛫🏖️

* I am the luckiest person to be surrounded by the best friends. So grateful for you all 👯‍♀️

* Being able to exercise and work out my body 💪 Can’t wait to put more of this into my life in 2024!

* My ❤️

One of the most common misconceptions in sourdough is…

“I’m too busy to make sourdough!” 

As a mom of two, I’m here to encourage you and say, it is possible to make sourdough, even in a busy schedule.

Let me show you how! 🍞

With just a little planning, you can create a thriving sourdough starter from scratch in the nooks and crannies of your day. 

Seriously, it only takes 2 minutes a day. 🙌🏻Sounds doable, right? 

Plus, I have a FREE guide that I can send you to make your very own sourdough starter from scratch even easier. More on that later 😉

Cheddar & Chive Sourdough Biscuits 🧀🌿

Homemade sourdough biscuits have to be one of my favorite recipes. 

Not only are they one of the quickest ways to get fresh, hot bread on the table, but they are SO tasty.

My Sourdough Biscuit recipe got a delicious upgrade! 😍😋

 Every buttery, flaky bite is now met with melty cheddar cheese, freshly chopped chives, and aromatic garlic! 

It’s like Red Lobster’s beloved Cheddar Bay Biscuits, but even better because it’s made with the goodness of sourdough! 

This recipe is totally customizable to incorporate your favorite flavors, so feel free to mix and match your favorite cheeses, fresh or dried herbs, and spices.

Has this ever happened to you?

You slice into your freshly baked sourdough sandwich bread to find a huge hole near the top of your crust.

Unlike artisan sourdough loaves, where holes in their crumb is preferred (the perfect place to hold extra butter 🤭), a sourdough sandwich loaf should have a tight crumb with minimal holes. 

Luckily, this is an easy fix! All you need to do is degas your dough! 

The best way to degas your dough is to punch the dough multiple times with your fist, just like you see in the video. This releases all of those large the air bubbles that were created during the bulk fermentation. 

You will also want to shape your dough nice and tight, further removing air bubbles, creating a tight, uniform crumb. 

Looking for an easy and delicious sourdough sandwich bread recipe? Comment BREAD(🍞) and I’ll send the link to mine directly to you!

Blueberry Lemon Poppy Seed Sourdough Muffins 🫐🍋

These Blueberry Lemon Poppy Seed Sourdough Muffins are pulling out all the stops! It’s the only sourdough muffin recipe you’ll need this spring! 

Each bite is Full of bright tartness from the fresh lemon juice and a nutty texture from the poppy seeds. Then you’ll find a warm, plump blueberry! 

Made with sourdough discard, these sourdough muffins are so light and fluffy, you won’t be able to stop at just one muffin! 

Then, each bakery-style muffin with a sweet crumble topping and lemon glaze. They are so delicious! 

They’re the perfect muffin to start off your morning or to enjoy as a quick snack.

With Easter just 2 days away, it’s time to feed the starter and get baking!! 

Here’s a list of just a few of my favorite sourdough recipes that I know that you and your guests will love at your Easter Brunch or Dinner celebrations! 

🥕Sourdough Au Gratin Potatoes - Okay, here me out. Tender potatoes covered in a melty cheese sauce thickened with sourdough discard, and baked until golden brown and delicious. Are you drooling?! Better yet, this side dish is quick and easy to make!

🥕 Sourdough Hot Cross Buns - Cloud-like sourdough buns are lightly sweetened and bursting with flavor from warm spices, fresh orange zest, and plump raisins. These can be baked in the same day! 

🥕 Sourdough Carrot Cake - My mother’s super moist and flavorful carrot cake, now with the goodness of sourdough! Topped with a luscious cream cheese frosting for the perfect Easter dessert. 

🥕 Sourdough Lemon Bars - Bright and zesty, these Sourdough Lemon Bars are sure to brighten your day. Sweet and buttery sourdough shortbread is topped with a lemony curd and sprinkled with powdered sugar - these won’t last long! 

🥕 Sourdough Dinner Rolls - These rolls are perfect for any celebration! They are light, fluffy, tearable, and shareable! Prepare the dough and bake them up fresh all in the same day. They would also make for delicious ham sandwiches with leftovers!

Before delivering my second, one ofp my nesting goals was to pack the freezer with all things sourdough! 

Now a few weeks postpartum, I’m so glad that I did! 

Freezing sourdough is really simple and has allowed me and my family to still enjoy our favorite sourdough recipes, while I take a break from baking it fresh. 

And in all honesty, everything tastes just as good as they do when freshly baked/made! 

Here’s some tips to freezing/reheating:

- Make sure the item is fully cooled before putting the into the freezer. 

You don’t want condensation in the freezer bag, otherwise that can affect the texture. 

- Pre-slice your sourdough bread, sandwich bread, bagels, and English muffins for easy reheating! 

I love to pop a frozen slice or two straight into the toaster - tastes like they’re freshly made every time!

-Make a double batch!

A great way to stock your freezer with sourdough is by making double batches. Enjoy one fresh, while saving the other for the future. 

Want the recipes? Comment FREEZER and I’ll send links to all my sourdough favorites directly to you!

Sourdough Au Gratin Potatoes 🥔

Thinly sliced potatoes are covered in a creamy, cheesey sauce, and then baked until the potatoes are tender and the sauce is bubbly. 

Are you drooling yet?!

I used freshly shredded Gruyere and Parmesan cheese, which brings such depth of flavor - it’s simply delicious 🧀

But what makes this version sourdough?

In a traditional Au Gratin recipe, melted butter and flour are used to make a roux, which helps to thicken this cheese sauce. However, this recipes skips this step, and instead, uses sourdough discard as the thickener!

It’s the perfect no-waste solution that also brings a slight tang to the party! 

This recipe would be perfect for a cozy weeknight dinner or for your Easter celebration! 

Want the recipe? Comment 🥔 (POTATO) and I’ll send it directly to you!

Sourdough Hot Cross Buns 🍞

These long-fermented sourdough buns are something special! 

They are super soft, like a cloud, tearable and shareable. Each bite is bursting with flavor from the plump raisins, fresh orange zest, and warm spices like cinnamon and all spice. 

They are perfectly delicious when served warm with a generous slab of salty butter! 

Traditionally, they are baked up yearly on Good Friday, but they are delicious enough to be enjoyed all year long. 

Their name comes from their trademark - a cross pattern piped on top with a water/flour mixture. 

Better yet, this recipe can be prepared and baked in the same day! I even included two example baking schedules.

If you know me, then you know I’m not a huge spender and I’m not quick fo buy just out of convenience. 

For the first year of making sourdough, I practiced making bread with the bare minimum and was just fine.

But over the years, I have invested in a few more tools to help make the sourdough process a little more clean, quick, and conveneient. 

One of these tools are aren’t totally necessary, but I have grown to really appreciate and love are my bowl scrapers!

This simple tool does just as the name describes, scrapes the bowl! Why is that helpful? 

It helps to combine ALL of you ingredients, instead of losing some that gets stuck to the sides of the bowl.

It also helps to make your sourdough process a little cleaner, as you can use it to clean up the sides of your mixing bowl and your hands. 

Better yet, this tool is such a CHEAP investment! I bought a set of two for less than $5! 

Want your very own? Comment LINK and I’ll send you my favorite bowl scraper right to you.

🥕 Sourdough Carrot Cake 🥕

With Easter just around the corner, I’ve been pulling out family recipes and giving them a sourdough update! 

One of the most recent recipes I’ve been experimenting with is my mother’s carrot cake recipe, which she made every Easter.

Friends, it’s truly a winner!!

This super moist, sourdough carrot cake is bursting with flavor from warm spices like ground cinnamon and a slight tang from the sourdough discard.

I know nuts in desserts aren’t everyone’s cup of tea, but I love the extra texture chopped pecans bring to this cake. So add or omit to your preferences!

Then to top off this delicious dessert is a luscious, homemade cream cheese frosting. 

I’m sure that this easy-to-make dessert will be an instant crowd-pleaser for you and your guests this Easter season!

Sourdough Irish Soda Bread ☘️ 

This quick bread is the perfect addition to your St. Patrick’s Day Celebration! 

The inclusions of sharp cheddar cheese, chopped chives, and garlic powder brings such delicious, savory flavors that would pair perfectly with a beef stew or corned beef and cabbage! 

Plus, it’s such a quick and easy recipe to whip together with sourdough discard. Bake it in a cast iron or baking sheet until golden brown and beautiful.

Slice while warm and cover generously with your favorite Irish butter…yum! 😋

If you’re looking for a more traditional take, you could also omit these inclusions and keep it plain or add raisins! This sweeter version is delicious when served with butter and your favorite jam. 

Want the recipe? Comment LINK and I’ll send the link directly to you! 

**Link will be sent to your DMs, so make sure to check all your folders! 🤍**

STORY TIME.
Many years ago, my mom- Sheeja Pillai dreamt of starting her very own playschool for kids. Her love for kids and teaching goes way back in time. She has still safely kept all my nursery and preschool worksheets for her to refer in future for her own students. But somewhere along the years, she got busy with her own work and family. But this dream still remained within her heart. She helped me and all her students pursue all our dreams. She’s an amazing mom, friend, daughter, sister but she’s the BEST TEACHER one will ever know. I have seen her students talk about her and that’s how I know she’s every student’s favourite teacher. This woman has taught kids all her life and she’s hands down the best at it. I am lucky to have her as my mother/mentor/teacher/friend. She’s the person who taught me to dream and aim to fulfil your dream. Now I think it’s time for her to do the same. TODOBORO is amma’s new born baby who needs all your blessings and good wishes. I’ve seen you excited, nervous, panicking and figuring things out all on your own since the very first day. This is just the first step amma, you’ve got a long road ahead. I know it’s gonna be a bumpy ride but I am literally in the next room, all you have to do is scream- REVU and I will be there. So to conclude this, amma all the very best, do what you do, because you’re the best at it. I love you and now TODOBORO from the bottom of my heart.🩵

Unlearning the all-or-nothing mentality many of us live by (whether we like it or not!!) is one of the biggest hurdles we ADHDers face once we learn what’s been going on in our brains all this time.

We try to learn everything we can about ADHD.

We try strategies.

We still don’t understand why they aren’t working. 

Why we keep “failing.” 

BUT ✨WE✨ ARE NOT FAILING!

OUR ✨STRATEGIES✨ ARE FAILING!!

Because so often even the strategies we try to implement for our ADHD still have an underlying current of all-or-nothing. 

📣This is one of the MOST important things to work on as you start to build a more ADHD-friendly life. 

It’s something I work on myself still every day!

And I focus heavily on this with all my 1:1 ADHD coaching clients AND in my new ADHD Strategy Building Course✨🙌

Because what good is an ADHD strategy if it’s no use for us when our day doesn’t go “to plan”? 

➡️Struggling with this? You’re not alone. Many of us are — and I’d love to support you! Here’s how:

📆 1:1 ADHD Coaching slots now open for end of May & June!✨

OR

🔔Join my ADHD Strategy Building Course — enrollment now open!🎉

🔗All details found at link in bio @adhdcoach.rosie 

Here’s me sending an adaptable day your way🧡

Hello hello! How is your May going? I’ve been taking advantage of the fairly decent weather and continuing to build my life here in Bielefeld…including creating new + adapting old ADHD strategies for myself!

This has been so fun as behind the scenes I’m simultaneously creating my ADHD Strategy Building Course (can’t wait for you to dive in next week if you’ve already joined!✨🎉)

Life lately: 

1. Spring in Germany: when you take advantage of 60° F (15° C) days by rotating between a leather jacket + scarf and a sports bra every 15 min. based on the wind-to-sun ratio🌬️🌤️

2. One of my oldest and bestest besties popped over for a spontaneous visit from the UK🧡 

Thanks to Deutsche Bahn, within an hour he learned that certain German stereotypes do not hold true (IYKYK). 
3. 🌷 
4. 🌤️

5. Other people at volleyball that day: “How long have you guys been friends?”….

Me: [checks watch; looks at Mo]… “18 hours?”✨ 
6. Back at @bielefelduniversity for the first time since finishing my MA in 2018!

7. One of my fave things about being back is actually a person👯‍♀️ 
8. Deadlifting brings me joy even when weak AF⚡️ 

9. When you only see people you love every few years, neither has the patience for proper pics, so you take advantage of all reflective surfaces for selfies😆✨

10. That day when, in the midst of creating my ADHD Strategy Building Course, I worked from an indoor desk, outdoor table, a sofa, a call cubicle, aand a spinny chair…all in the name of keeping my brain on track. And it worked! 

And to think I never thought of myself as hyperactive, just because I also have sloth/potato days😅

➡️ On that note, if you’re also trying to build an ADHD-friendly life for yourself, I’d love to support you! 

Click the bio link for @adhdcoach.rosie to work with me 1:1, or to join my new ADHD Strategy Building course coming next week!💫🪄🧠🔗 •

I had cold, leftover homemade Pad Thai for breakfast today. Couldn’t have asked for a better brekkie🙌 

I recorded this a while ago while still in Berlin, but at LEAST once a week (usually more) I wake up craving last night’s dinner and absolutely nothing else sounds appealing. 

So many of us have these rigid ideas in our heads of what a “good” breakfast is, or what foods we can eat at which times of day. 

But do you know what the BEST breakfast is? 

The one you’ll actually eat!! 

Is there a healthier brekkie option than tuna pesto pasta, or leftover Pad Thai?

Obviously. 

Was I going to eat it this morning? At least without a lot of time wasted debating myself? 

No.

Absolutely not🤣

➡️ Learning how we can live our lives in a way that best supports our brains requires a LOT of unlearning. 

Unlearning these rigid ideas we have about how our lives “should” look. 

What we “should” do. 

And what it “should” look like while we do it. 

Because let’s face it…we’ve been trying to fit into those “shoulds” our whole lives…and for most of us, all it’s done is led to burnout, exhaustion, and shame. 

🪄So let’s try something different together, shall we?!

This is a huge part of what we work on together in 1:1 ADHD Coaching, and will also be a big part of the DIY ADHD Strategy Building course I’ll be launching soon🎉

⚡️If you want to learn HOW to build sustainable, adaptable strategies to support your ADHD, I’ll be showing you the process I use myself + with all my clients in this course.

Some of the most helpful + life-changing strategies I use in my every day life for my ADHD may seem simple to an outside perspective. 

To you this might just look like a woman wearing gloves to pack boxes. 

The reality? 

It’s a strategy I use regularly so my brain doesn’t get exhausted and shut down from simply needing to touch certain materials. 

Wearing these gloves to pack means all that energy I would’ve used to suffer through packing (it would’ve been a lottt) I could put towards packing longer, socializing, or even better, actually RESTING. 

But strategies like this took me DECADES to figure out. 

I moved 37 times before I started wearing gloves to pack😱

Not because I didn’t have gloves. I did! 

Not because cardboard didn’t bother me. It really (REALLY) did😩

But because I was so used to EVERYTHING being a monumental battle. I was absolutely EXHAUSTED. 

My brain couldn’t even fathom the ways I could adapt things in my life (big yes, but especially small!) to help my brain out. 

🔜 This is why I’m creating an ADHD Strategy Building course for ADHDers like me - like you! 

Because I know how life-changing these strategies can be, and the ripple effect they have on your day and life. 

⚡️Want to learn HOW to build sustainable, adaptable strategies to support your ADHD? I’ll be showing you the process I use myself + with all my 1:1 ADHD Coaching clients in this course.

Hello hello! Missed your faces🧡 Before jumping into ADHD Coaching content, here’s some life happenings…

I moved cities mid-March, but didn’t expect half of my first 6 weeks would be paired with tonsillitis + my first ever round of Covid. 

Being sick is bad for your health health but my God is it bad for my mental health —you can unfortunately probs relate!

Besides supporting my ADHD Coaching clients (which always brings me joy no matter what — you guys are my peopleee🥹), I’ve been working on helping my brain out.

But I am so so happy to back in my (German) hometown💛 

It’s gotten me so inspired…including a new course I’m super stoked about for you DIYers🎉 

Life lately: 
1. First floor sits in my new flat. Floor sits are the best sits. 

2. Seeing this photo raised my heart-rate. Very glad I don’t have to move again for ::checks stress levels:: another 5 months. 

3. First night back in Bielefeld. So happy. So blissfully unaware that in 2 hours tonsillitis would be back with full force.  

4. First time back in the gym in…4 months? Very weak. Very many lost muscles. Very happy camper being back at it. 

5. First flat in Germany was around the corner. No stream back then. You’d think after Berlin’s Spree it wouldn’t be a big deal. BUT YOU WOULD BE WRONG. THIS LUTTER BRINGS ME SO MUCH JOY!  

6. Fave local takeaway + Ted Lasso. Minus the Covid, I would’ve had a blast.  

7. Found the 4 pairs of Busan socks I bought when visiting where I used to live in Korea again back in 2017. Also joy-giving.

8. I rarely ever match. I rarely ever wear or have seafoam green. Seeing this reflection was…jarring. 

9. Also jarring. I know I lived in Medellín, but like many things, if it’s not top of mind, I often forget. (My love of clouds clearly pre-dated decent camera quality.)

10. Pod time at my new coworking space, cooking up the details for the course I’m working on for you guys! 

➡️ Want to learn to build sustainable strategies for your ADHD? This one's for you! 

🔗Waitlist link is in my bio for first dibs + deets!🔗

In a sea of FB ads, your headline is your first impression. It's the one thing that cuts through the noise and grabs attention. 

Advertising legend Ogilvy said the headline is the most important part of an ad.

In fact, studies indicate that nearly five times as many people read the headline as they read the body copy. If people don’t like the headline, they stop reading…period.

Good headlines spark curiosity, hook your target audience, highlight value, and increase conversion rates.

Learn these lessons the easy way:

1. Quantity matter just as much as quality. And not for the reason you think.

We tend to focus so much on WHAT we are posting and way to little on HOW MUCH we are posting.

Because you need TIME and PRACTICE to figure out what works for you. Your first post will suck, and that’s okay. The more you post the better you will get.

2. The algortiham is not your enemy. The infamous Instagram algorithm is getting blamed left and right for underperformance, but the truth is

ALGORITHM = PEOPLE

Your audience and what they do when they see your content determines how the algortiham will respond to your content.

3. Consistency doesn’t just mean being consistent in how many times you post a week. It also means being consistent with your messaging and content.

Repurposing and reposting the same content and messages is not only beneficial because it saves time but also because it help you set up your brand.

Nobody remembers what you posted on Instagram 3 months ago I promise. Go repurpose that content.

4. The people that will end up buying from you and sign up to work with you - might not follow you at all.

The biggest surprise I ever got was getting messages and calls from people never ever showed up in my notifications. Not even a like or a follow.

That goes to show - those metrics don’t mean nothing for your business.

5. The only people that never saw success on Instagram are the ones that gave up too soon.

This goes for pretty much everything in life but it’s soo true with Instagram as well.

That doesn’t mean you need to just post what you’ve always posted if it doesn’t work - it means you adapt and adjust until you find your thing.

Turn these on today 👇

1. Set up your business or creator profile.This will help you track your insights - a crucial part of your strategy.

2. Message and story replies settings.You want to turn these on to make sure anyone can message you and reply to your stories because you don’t want to miss out on potential clients or customers by being unavailable for their questions.

3. Like and share counts. This is a controversial one, but you can choose to hide the like and share counts on all of your posts on your account.

If your niche or industry doesn’t really care about those metrics and you want people to focus on more on the content, then the numbers feel free to hide your like and share counts.

4. Show account suggestions on profiles. You can only turn this setting on desctop and not on the Instagram app.

But it basically allows your profile to show up as a suggestion when somebody follows a similar account on Instagram, and it also allows other profiles to show up as suggestions when somebody follow you.

5. High-quality uploads for reels. This is a must-have setting for reels that can really make your reels not perform very well if you don’t have it turned on.

6. Posts lowered in feed. Go to your Settings and peivacy - Accaunt status to check if any of your posts have been flagged and lowered in feed.

7. Welcome message. You can set up a welcome message that appear to people when they try to DM you, this is a place to show your brand voice and start conversation with people.

8. Frequently asked questions. In order to make it even easier for people to reach out, you can set up questions they can just tap on and send. I would put in your FAQ here and some questions about your services you want people to ask you.

10. Saved message replies. To make it easier to reply to those messages then you can save the answers to those questions, links and info you would need so you can respond to your DMs freqently so your audience doesn’t wait and Instagram give you a badge of “usually responds within 1 hour”.

Please STOP mindlessly commenting on others’ posts.

I see too many people leaving generic comments and failing to engage meaningfully.

Do this instead:

- Read the entire post before commenting to understand the context.
- Share your thoughts, experiences, or ask a thoughtful question.
- Tailor your responses to each post, avoiding one-size-fits-all replies.
- Show appreciation or add value with your comment.

The main reason for failure: Generic comments don’t foster real engagement or connections.

Save your time, engage with intent, and build meaningful relationships.

Let’s break it down 👇

But first.. SAVE this before you scroll away and lose this checklist:

01. Hook

Check, your reel has a good hook in there first 2 seconds.

Visual, text and audio hooks determine if people will stick around to your post.

Nothing else matters if people are scrolling away in the first 2 seconds.

02. Goal

One piece of content can’t be reposible for everything.

There are 3 main goals your content needs to accomplish: attract new people, build trust with your audience, convert them to take action (sign up for your email list, check out your website or DM you about your offers)

03. Call To Action

Match your call to action on your post to your goal and make it as simple as possible for your audience.

but first.. SAVE this before you scroll away and lose them 👇

1. Create content that your audience wants to engage with. Posts that invoke negative emotional reactions are the most engaging.

2. DM peope additional free value if they comment a certain word on the posts (see below for my example)

3. Reply to your comments with questions. That way, you get 2 comments from 1 engaged person.

4. Like and respond to past posts when you post something new. That way, your engaged audience gets a notification from you.

5. Share your posts to stories with a CTA that will get people to engage. Not a huge sticker to cover your post that says “new post”.

6. Use a “like” as a call to action on relatable content and “save” on valuable content.

caption:
In 2020, I found Bright on my Instagram explore page, looking helpless and clueless about why his parents left him tied to a pole all alone. 
His eyes were deep and full of questions.. I couldnt help myself from reaching out to the adoption appeal and meet him! In an instant I fell in love with him and he with me. Got him home, and the rest is history 

My baby kishmish is another miracle that happened in my life. Last year I was shooting in Mahabaleshwar for my show highway love for @amazonminitv , and on the deserted road just outside my vanity van I heard a puppy whining. It was raining outside and she was bleeding.. maybe a bite wound? I obviously couldn’t leave her there.. she came to me at a time when I needed her the most. Our meeting was divine. Thank God for the team of people I worked with who were just as forthcoming about helping her. I obviously got her back with me to her forever home. Both my babies are godsend and I have more love in my life than I ever imagined possible. ❤️

ADOPT, DON’T SHOP. 
Thank you @mamaearth.in @feminaindia for this award✨

Why is starting so hard?

I’ve decided to make my SwiftUI app that I created last year called GamesFinder in Jetpack Compose.

I created the layout of folders, went through the old SwiftUI project but when I sat down to start I stalled. I’m not sure if it’s because I know the end goal and the sheer size of it or because I’ve done this app before. Maybe starting is just that hard 😅

I’ll share with you start to finish in details on how I’m making this app. Hopefully, you can learn from both from my wins and my mistakes 💪

caption:
My passions for programming hasn’t gone away, but when it does falters, I draw strength from my stubbornness 😅
Without this trait, I wouldn’t have come this far or know what I do today. 
What is your secret weapon to stay on track? 💜

Happy Thursday! 💜

#100daysofswiftui 

I’m doing the #100daysofcodechallenge as we have 93 days left of the year. 

I’m using the Hacking with Swift website (hackingwithswift.com) which has a section specifically for this challenge. It has days 1-100 so you’ll never have to worry about what to do.

The rules are to do at least 1h of SwiftUI every day and to post about it to keep yourself accountable. 

I’m on day 10 and will mostly be doing my updates on my stories. 

With less than 100 days left in 2022 maybe it’s time to pick up a new skill using the #100days challenge. 

💬Have you ever done the #100daysofcode or a similar challenge? What did you think? 

💜Happy coding!💜

Wireframe

💬 Have you ever heard about wireframes or created one before?

We’re doing UI/UX design at school and were told to do wireframing of our app. This is the first “look” at the very early stages of my SwiftUI app. (if you want to follow my app’s journey go and check out my GitHub for updates). 

So what are wireframes? 

Wireframe is a two-dimensional skeletal outline of an app or webpage, they show the structure and user flow.

Wireframes are used early in the development process to establish the basic structure of a page before visual design and content are added.

You can draw them by hand (like I did) or created them digitally. 

There are three main types of wireframes: low-fidelity wireframes(what I did), mid-fidelity wireframes, and high-fidelity wireframes. The most significant distinguishing factor between these wireframes is the amount of detail they contain.

Happy Friday!! 💜

🔹Documentation🔹

💬When do you read the documentation?

🔹Tbh I always google my problems and most of the time Google gives me StackOverflow. This is a quick and easy way to get an answer to the issue at hand but if I still don’t understand what the code is doing that's when I head over to the documentation and do a deep dive into the matter.

🔹I find that this way I can narrow down the problem which makes it easier to find what I’m looking for in the documentation otherwise I might spend way too much time just searching and struggling to find the right section. 

🔹So my steps are: Try to figure it out myself (you learn so much by breaking the code) → StackOverflow → Documentation → cry 🥲

💜Happy Coding💜

💜Happy Monday💜

“The future depends on what you do today.” ~ Mahatma Gandhi

🔹It’s a new week so let’s set some new goals. I love to start the week with big clear goals which I then break down daily. 

🔹So for example This week I want to finish sections 11-14 of the Swift course. I will then do daily reviews on how my progress towards this goal is going and set small goals like how many hours I should focus on it that day so that at the end of the week, I will have achieved my goals.

💬Do you set monthly, weekly or daily goals for yourself?

Your iPhone passcode does NOT protect you as much as you think. 🔐 Here’s why you need to enable “Stolen Device Protection” immediately after installing iOS 17.3!

This feature does not impact your day-to-day usage, as it only forces Face ID/Touch ID when you are away from a familiar location, like home or work. 🏡

And when you ARE away from home or work and someone tries to change your Apple ID password, disable Find My, etc.. they’ll be hit with a double biometric authentication, with a 1-hour delay in between each scan. No thief will be waiting around for all of that, so enable this feature asap! 🔒📲

Bootstrapped vs Funded Business 🚀
Discover which strategy aligns best with your goals. 

🔍 Checklist: Choose the right business for you📋

1. Financial Risk Tolerance: Are you comfortable investing your own funds initially, or do you prefer external capital to accelerate growth?

2. Control vs. Expertise: Do you value complete control over your business decisions (bootstrapped), or are you open to leveraging the expertise and networks of investors (funded)?

3. Growth Pace: Are you content with a slower, organic growth trajectory (bootstrapped), or do you seek rapid expansion with the support of external funding (funded)?

4. Long-Term Vision: What are your long-term goals for the business? Does your strategy align more with a gradual, sustainable approach (bootstrapped), or aggressive scaling facilitated by funding (funded)?

5. Risk Appetite: How comfortable are you with the potential pressure to perform and meet investor expectations (funded), versus the autonomy and independence of self-funding (bootstrapped)?

Evaluate these factors to determine which type of business aligns best with your goals, preferences, and risk tolerance🚀
.

Stop using outdated tools when Amazon has opened its treasure chest for you. And it’s free.  

Zero points for guessing I’m talking about Amazon Pi.

Pi is Amazon’s AI-powered analytics solution that provides sellers with customized insights and recommendations tailored to their specific business needs. 

While Pi has numerous applications, let me highlight a game-changing feature that can revolutionize your Amazon sales:

 📍 “Market Basket Analysis” 

It analyzes every purchase your customers make on the days they buy your product.  

In short, you can identify complementary products to cross-sell. 

For example, if Pi shows that your customers often buy product X after buying yours, you can strategically place ads for your product on X’s detail pages.

Here’s how you can leverage this data: 

📌 Low-risk product market testing

→ With Pi’s advanced analytics, you can test promoting your product in new categories with low ad bids. 

→ This data-driven approach minimizes risk as you validate untapped customer segments.

📌 Brand level targeting

→ If Pi shows that your customers tend to buy from certain brands after purchasing your product, you can focus your advertising on those brands to capture more of that existing demand.

📌 Optimized product bundles

→ Pi’s AI can recommend compelling product bundles by analyzing purchase correlations. 

→ By bundling complementary items, you can increase your AOV and customer lifetime value.

I recommend using Pi’s insights at least once a month to refine your advertising, promotion, and inventory strategies based on emerging customer behavior patterns.

Amazon Pi is your built-in AI co-pilot to accelerate your brand’s growth. 

Are you using it the right way? 
.

Disover Amazon’s three diverse shipping options to cater to your unique needs? 📦 

Here’s what you might not have known:

1. Easy Ship: Amazon’s hassle-free solution where they handle the entire shipping process, from packing to delivery, allowing you to focus on growing your business while they take care of logistics.

2. Self Ship: Take control of your shipping process by managing packing, labeling, and scheduling pickups yourself. This option provides flexibility and autonomy for businesses with specific shipping preferences.

3. Amazon FBA (Fulfillment by Amazon): Leverage Amazon’s extensive fulfillment network by sending your inventory to Amazon’s warehouses. They handle storage, packing, and shipping of your products, along with customer service and returns, streamlining your operations and expanding your reach.

Know your options and optimize your shipping strategy to meet your business goals effectively on the world’s largest online marketplace! 🚚💼

Maximize your Amazon profits with this ingenious hack! Here’s how it works: 

1. Capture Evidence: Whenever you receive a return from a customer, whether it’s an item that’s damaged, fake, or not as described, make sure to document it thoroughly. Take clear photos or videos showcasing the condition of the returned item.

2. Apply for Safe-T Claims: Navigate to the manager orders section on your Amazon seller dashboard. Here, you’ll find the option to apply for Safe-T Claims. This feature allows you to request compensation for eligible returns that have caused you financial losses.

3. Choose Wisely: Keep in mind that you can only claim Safe-T for up to 10% of your orders. So, it’s essential to select the returns that have the most significant impact on your profits. Prioritize claims for items with significant damages or those that are clearly counterfeit.

4. Secure Your Earnings: By utilizing Safe-T Claims, you’re taking proactive steps to protect your earnings as an Amazon seller. Rather than absorbing losses from fake returns, you’re leveraging Amazon’s policies to seek reimbursement for legitimate grievances.

Don’t let fake returns eat into your hard-earned profits. Take control of your seller experience with this strategic approach. Happy selling!🚀💰

I’ve never talked about this before.

It was the beginning of August, and I was 9 months pregnant with my 3rd child when I received a message from an AWS recruiter. At that time I was already planning to move inside Accenture to the cloud org. 

I felt as I couldn’t miss this opportunity. I didn’t tell the AWS recruiter about my pregnancy, as I had faced discrimination in the past, so I went ahead and scheduled my interview for August 26th, which happened to be a day after my daughter was born. 

The 1st interview went great and I scheduled my technical interviews 3 weeks apart so I could prepare between them. I started building hands-on projects in during baby naps. It all was going fine until…

September 16th, I received a call informing me that my father had died... I don’t think that at that time I could really process how I felt and what was happening around me. It was kind of pretending that everything was fine - and just trying to do it all: organize funerals, take care of a newborn, and prepare for interviews.

I remember cheering myself up as I was passing from one interview stage to another, as this whole prep process actually kept me sane.

On December 15th, when my daughter was 3.5 months old, I joined AWS, and it was the first day when they found out I had a baby.

I didn’t have a lot of real-world implementation experience, so in my interviews, I talked about my side projects.

For those who are in a similar situation and want to transition to the cloud but don’t get a chance to work on AWS projects at their current job, I created a list with 3 AI projects to get started (using Bedrock, PartyRock, Amazon Q, serverless)

🔗 Comment “CAREER” and I will send you links to 3 projects that include step-by-step guidance.

I’ve been with AWS 3+ years now. I truly love my job, and I think that this passion is what helped me to built 500K+ community and opened opportunities to share my expertise as an international AWS speaker and content creator  helping to upskill hundreds of thousands people around the world ♥️🌎👫👭🏽👬

I hope my story will inspire others who face doubts and challenges to persevere despite them ✨

Let me know if you have any questions.
