One of the biggest things that took me from being a very anxious person to a pretty calm person was realizing that I was never stuck.

We are always living in the feeling of our thinking and because of the fluid nature of thought we are only and always one that away from all new experience.

I used to be so scared of feeling anxious of having any uncomfortable feeling that I tried to control my experience.

I would resist and hold on tight afraid that if I relaxed I would feel anxious and lose control.

It was life-changing when I realized that when I let go I fell out of resistance and fell out of anxiety and effortlessly moved to a better feeling.

It was life-changing when I realized it was safe to relax. It was safe not to think so much. Letting go of control and knowing that my thoughts and experience are designed to flow all in their own changed my life and gave me the freedom that I was looking for.

Anxiety can be a temptation for me. Worry can be a temptation for me. Controlling can be a temptation for me.

I used to worry so much and try to control situations. I didn’t know it was possible to love without fear.

There were times when I felt like it was worth it for me to be worried and miserable because somebody had to worry to keep everybody safe.

A couple years ago I realized that carefree isn’t careless. I realized it was safe not to think so much. I realized that anxious thinking is distorted thinking.

I realized you can never get enough of what you don’t need and controlling a situation isn’t going to give me the true sense of safety that I’m looking for.

I know that I made of wisdom and common sense which will always be available to me at the precise moment I needed and never a moment before. 

I often scroll away from videos I know aren’t going to be helpful for me in having a sense of trust, safety and a quiet mind.

What if you see setbacks as a sign of progress and not something to fight or get down about? 

What if you could be happy because you’re starting to see that there’s no right or wrong way to feel and this was how you were meant to feel in this moment. 

What if you stopped labeling any feeling as wrong?

When you stop resisting your experience (feeling anxious and uncomfortable) you see how capable you are and that you’re never stuck. 

When you see how capable and fluid your experiences, you’re free!

After I had my first panic attack which involved the realization and depersonalization, I ramped up how much I was doing for my mental health. I focused even more on getting enough sleep. I ate even “cleaner“. I meditated more. Twice a day. I journal. I tried all different types of therapy for extended periods of time. I tried to exercise but not too much. In essence I became obsessed with anxiety and my mental health. 

I felt like my mental health was so fragile and my life became smaller and smaller and anxiety and panic we’re almost all I thought about. 

I was afraid to watch a TV show with my husband at the time because I was afraid of the blue light and that I needed to get at least eight hours or else I could panic.

I would look at other people and be so envious that they seem so normal.

I felt so broken because I was doing everything that was recommended and yet I felt worse and worse. 

Everything changed for me when I realized that I wasn’t broken and the only problem was that I was innocently over complicating my well-being. 

Everything I was doing wasn’t “working” because it was adding stress and even more thinking, obsessing, and introspection.

Human beings have the best in built healing system. When you understand anxiety and stop resisting it and stop trying to think your way out of it you’re not in a stress response as much. You’re more in your life than in your head. Because you’re not in a state of fight or flight as much your body actually has time to heal. Your body knows how to heal from all the physical symptoms that you’ve been experiencing. You are designed beautifully and designed to come back into balance.

The reason that I had physical symptoms for so long and had so many was because I didn’t know about this and I kept obsessing and researching and innocently over complicating mental and physical well-being. 

Once I came into the three principles understanding, which is what I base my coaching on, my physical symptoms started to fall away. Some sooner than others but within a year every single symptom was gone. Some that I’d experience since childhood and just thought was how I was made. I had headaches since before I could swallow a pill. I had stomach aches since elementary school. I struggled with IBS for decades trying so many illumination diets, supplements, medicines, seeing specialists. Remember the last time I had a headache or a stomachache. My digestion is perfect. I never even thought that was possible. I just thought maybe some of my other symptoms like I floaters and difficulty breathing would fall away. Oh, I also thought I was someone who would always struggle without insomnia. Not true. For the past five years sleep has come so easily to me! 

I’ll stop talking about my symptoms, but what I want you to know is if this is possible for you. There is nothing special about me. 

PS the symptom that took the longest to go away was what I’d call my breathing thing. I would hold my breath unintentionally then notice and breathe deeply and then would get stuck in the cycle of very labored breathing and focus on my breathing. It lasted so long because I kept checking on it. I kept using it as a marker to see when I would be fully healed…continued in comments

What if the very fact that we’re feeling anxious shows us that we should take everything we think with a grain of salt because it’s most likely untrue? 

What if you could take great care of yourself without feeling anxious?

What if you didn’t have to be on guard? What if you could see that when you were hypervigilant and on guard for any physical symptoms you tended to get confused about whether it’s anxiety or something serious? 

What if you could see that it was safe not to think so much and that your wisdom in common sense always had your back? 

*please note this is when you’ve been checked by your doctor and when you’re not anxious know your symptoms are because of anxiety. I never want anyone to chalk up your physical sensations to anxiety before talking to a doctor. *

caption: mirror selfie saga

Had a chill day at Moonstone Hammock’s Forest Cabin in Karjat, where I tried kayaking for the first time. 
The high tea and dinner offerings were 👩‍🍳💋 & the service was super friendly. Played some badminton with the staff, who were really cool about joining in. Also did karaoke, took a dip in the pool, and ended the day with a movie night. The place is right by the river, so the sunset view was beautiful. Definitely worth checking out.
